main event: A group of 10-12 white, round objects were sighted in a staggered formation flying south over Cresco, Iowa on July 27, 1964.
interesting points: The objects were observed for 10-15 seconds before disappearing over the horizon.
The witness, a 38-year-old gas company employee, was on an astronomy trip when he noticed the objects.
The sighting occurred on the edge of a thunderstorm with lightning in the area.
No sound was reported from the objects.
No interceptor aircraft were in the area at the time of the sighting.
